title: Google\Cloud\Dlp\V2\StorageConfig_TimespanConfig
name: StorageConfig_TimespanConfig
description:
Configuration of the timespan of the items to include in scanning.

Currently only supported when inspecting Google Cloud Storage and BigQuery.

methods.name: getTimestampField
methods.description:
Specification of the field containing the timestamp of scanned items.

Required for data sources like Datastore or BigQuery. The valid data types of the timestamp field are: for BigQuery - timestamp, date, datetime; for Datastore - timestamp. Datastore entity will be scanned if the timestamp property does not exist or its value is empty or invalid.

methods.name: getEnableAutoPopulationOfTimespanConfig
methods.description:
When the job is started by a JobTrigger we will automatically figure out a valid start_time to avoid scanning files that have not been modified since the last time the JobTrigger executed. This will be based on the time of the execution of the last run of the JobTrigger.
